column1: As a Helper I want to login to the UFund app so that I can access the needs cupboard and view my basket.
column2: **Given** I submit an existing username and CORRECT password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** I get a successful login attempt (200 code) and be redirected to the cupboard.
**Given** I submit an existing username and INCORRECT password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** I get a unsuccessful login attempt (401 code).

**Given** I submit a new username and password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** a user is created in the users.json file with an empty basket, I get a successful login attempt (200 code) and be redirected to the cupboard.

column1: AS A User I WANT the interface to be visually appealing and readable SO THAT I can easily navigate the U-Fund system.
column2: GIVEN the user opens any main page WHEN the UI loads THEN it should use consistent color scheme, fonts, and layout.

column1: AS A Helper I WANT to be notified when the inventory is updated SO THAT I can stay informed about new or changed inventory.
column2: GIVEN a new need is added or updated WHEN the inventory changes THEN the system should trigger a notification for all relevant users(helpers).
GIVEN no updates occur WHEN the user is active THEN no notification should be shown.

column1: AS A Helper I WANT to filter inventory items by category SO THAT I can quickly find specific needs.
column2: GIVEN I select a category WHEN viewing inventory THEN only matching needs should display.
GIVEN I select a filter WHEN viewing inventory THEN the list updates accordingly.
GIVEN I clear filters THEN all inventory items should as it did before again.

column1: AS A Developer I WANT to resolve overlap between cupboard and inventory data SO THAT only one system exists and displays consistent and accurate information.
column2: GIVEN I retrieve data from either cupboard or inventory, which I choose to keep, WHEN viewing needs THEN no duplicates.
GIVEN a need is fulfilled WHEN it moves from cupboard/inventory THEN the transition should be seamless and consistent.
GIVEN I check the backend data WHEN JSON is loaded THEN no data conflicts should occur.

column1: As a Helper I want to login to the UFund app so that I can access the needs cupboard and view my basket.
column2: **Given** I submit an existing username and CORRECT password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** I get a successful login attempt (200 code) and be redirected to the cupboard.
**Given** I submit an existing username and INCORRECT password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** I get a unsuccessful login attempt (401 code).

**Given** I submit a new username and password that isn't 'admin' into the login input **when** make a request to login **then** a user is created in the users.json file with an empty basket, I get a successful login attempt (200 code) and be redirected to the cupboard.

column1: As a Manager I want to log in with the reserved username admin so that I can access the admin dashboard and gain admin privileges.
column2: **Given** I input the username admin into the login page **when** I make a login request **then** I expect a successful login attempt (200 code) and be redirected to the admin dashboard.

GIVEN I submit the reserved username admin with an incorrect password. WHEN the system validates the credentials. THEN the login should fail, no access should be granted, and the system should return a status code of 401 (UNAUTHORIZED)

column1: As a User I WANT to log in and log out properly SO THAT I can securely access and exit my account.
column2: GIVEN a Helper enters valid credentials WHEN they click login THEN the system should authenticate and redirect them to their dashboard.
GIVEN a Helper clicks logout WHEN logged in THEN the system should end the session and return to the login page.
GIVEN invalid credentials are entered WHEN login is attempted THEN the system should display an error message and remain on the login screen.
